genresAdvancedInfo.name: danish techno
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Danish techno is a subgenre of techno music that originated in Denmark. It is characterized by its driving beats, minimalistic approach, and use of electronic instruments. The genre has been popularized by Danish DJs and producers such as Trentemøller and Kölsch.
